 :tx/rationale "ADR-FOUNDATION-031: THE INTROSPECTIVE OBSERVER. The daemon is not a performance optimization — it is the mechanism that makes C7 (self-bootstrap) actually true. Without persistent identity, braid cannot observe itself. The daemon enables reflexive divergence detection (Type 9): system vs system's-model-of-itself. Three converging insights crystallize: (1) ADR-029 connections-as-datoms — runtime observations ARE datoms with the same 6 lifecycle attributes. The connection between routing-latency and store-size IS a knowledge relationship that strengthens through co-activation and calibrates through hypothesis outcomes. (2) ADR-030 free energy gradient — F(S) applied to braid's own runtime. The store IS Q(s), the project IS P(o,s), but braid's runtime is ALSO P(o,s). The daemon computes F(S) over itself. (3) FEGH bridge hypotheses apply reflexively — when the self-model has disconnected clusters, spectral partition proposes bridges: 'what connects store loading to routing computation?' THIS is the question that would have prevented today's misdiagnosis. The fixed point: the system learns about itself using the same epistemological machinery it uses to learn about everything else. Four levels of reflexive observation (agent->project, braid->project, daemon->braid, calibration->daemon), each using the same three primitives (morphisms, reconciliation, acquisition function), each producing datoms that feed the level above."
